H:Water Procurement
P:Water is more important than food for survival.
P:Find water sources: streams, rivers, morning dew.
P:Always purify water before drinking.
P:Boiling is the most reliable method.

H:Shelter Building
P:Protection from elements is crucial.
P:Use natural materials: branches, leaves, rocks.
P:Build shelter before dark.
P:Insulate from ground to prevent heat loss.

H:Fire Making
P:Fire provides warmth, light, and cooking ability.
P:Collect dry tinder, kindling, and fuel wood.
P:Use friction methods or fire starter if available.
P:Maintain fire once started.

H:Food Sources
P:Plants: Learn to identify edible species.
P:Insects: High protein content.
P:Small game: Traps and snares.
P:Never eat unknown plants or mushrooms.

H:Signaling for Help
P:Create visible signals: smoke, mirrors, bright colors.
P:Use sound: whistle, shouting in patterns.
P:Ground signals: SOS, arrows pointing to location.
P:Stay in one place if rescue is likely.

Q:Remember: Stay calm, think clearly, prioritize needs.
